            "action_input": {
              "title": "API Developer Guide v2.1",
              "content": "# API Developer Guide v2.1\n\n## Overview\nThis guide provides comprehensive documentation for the API v2.1, including authentication, endpoints, rate limits, and best practices.\n\n## Base URL\n```\nhttps://api.example.com/v2\n```\n\n## Authentication\nAll API requests require authentication using Bearer tokens:\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN\n```\n\n### Obtaining an Access Token\n1. Register your application to receive client credentials\n2. Use the authentication endpoint to obtain tokens\n3. Include the token in the Authorization header for all requests\n\n## Rate Limits\n- **1000 requests per minute** per API key\n- Rate limit headers are included in all responses:\n  - `X-RateLimit-Limit`: Maximum requests allowed\n  - `X-RateLimit-Remaining`: Remaining requests in current window\n  - `X-RateLimit-Reset`: Time when limit resets (UTC timestamp)\n\n## HTTP Status Codes\n- `200 OK`: Successful request\n- `201 Created`: Resource created successfully\n- `400 Bad Request`: Invalid request parameters\n- `401 Unauthorized`: Invalid or missing authentication\n- `403 Forbidden`: Insufficient permissions\n- `404 Not Found`: Resource not found\n- `429 Too Many Requests`: Rate limit exceeded\n- `500 Internal Server Error`: Server error\n\n## Response Format\nAll responses are in JSON format with consistent structure:\n```json\n{\n  \"data\": {\n    // Response data\n  },\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n    \"version\": \"2.1\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Error Response Format\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"ERROR_CODE\",\n    \"message\": \"Human-readable error message\",\n    \"details\": {\n      // Additional error details\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Best Practices\n1. **Always implement retry logic** with exponential backoff\n2. **Cache responses** where appropriate to reduce API calls\n3. **Handle rate limits** by monitoring response headers\n4. **Validate requests** before sending to avoid unnecessary calls\n5. **Use pagination** for large datasets\n6. **Implement proper error handling** for all API calls\n\n## SDKs and Libraries\nOfficial client libraries are available for:\n- JavaScript/Node.js\n- Python\n- Java\n- PHP\n- Ruby\n\n## Support\n- Documentation: https://docs.example.com\n- API Status: https://status.example.com\n- Support Email: support@example.com\n- Community Forum: https://community.example.com\n\n## Versioning\nAPI versions follow semantic versioning. This documentation covers version 2.1. Backward compatibility is maintained within major versions.\n\n## Changelog\n### v2.1 (Current)\n- Added new endpoints for enhanced functionality\n- Improved error handling and response formats\n- Updated rate limiting policies\n- Enhanced security measures\n\n### v2.0\n- Complete API redesign\n- New authentication system\n- Improved performance and scalability"
