              "content": "# COMPANY RETREAT PROPOSAL\n\n## Executive Summary\nThis proposal outlines options for our annual company retreat in the San Francisco Bay Area, including venue recommendations, catering considerations, and budget planning.\n\n## Recommended Venue Options\n\n### 1. Cavallo Point Lodge (Sausalito)\n- **Location**: Just across the Golden Gate Bridge in Sausalito\n- **Capacity**: Accommodates up to 200 guests\n- **Features**: Historic military buildings, modern conference facilities, spa, and stunning bay views\n- **Ideal for**: Luxury retreats with team-building activities\n\n### 2. The Ritz-Carlton, Half Moon Bay\n- **Location**: Coastal setting 30 minutes from San Francisco\n- **Capacity**: Multiple meeting rooms for groups of various sizes\n- **Features**: Oceanfront views, golf courses, fire pits, and premium amenities\n- **Ideal for**: Executive retreats and strategic planning sessions\n\n### 3. Googleplex Conference Center (Mountain View)\n- **Location**: Silicon Valley heartland\n- **Capacity**: State-of-the-art facilities for tech companies\n- **Features**: Modern tech amenities, collaborative spaces, and innovation labs\n- **Ideal for**: Tech-focused companies and innovation workshops\n\n### 4. Claremont Club & Spa (Berkeley)\n- **Location**: Berkeley Hills with panoramic bay views\n- **Capacity**: Multiple event spaces for 20-500 guests\n- **Features**: Tennis courts, pools, spa, and extensive meeting facilities\n- **Ideal for**: Wellness-focused retreats with recreational activities\n\n## Catering Considerations\n\n### Dietary Requirements Note\n*Note: The team dietary requirements file was not accessible. Please ensure we obtain this information before finalizing catering arrangements.*\n\n### Recommended Approach:\n1. Survey all attendees for dietary restrictions and preferences\n2. Include vegetarian, vegan, gluten-free, and dairy-free options\n3. Consider local Bay Area cuisine featuring fresh, seasonal ingredients\n4. Plan for various meal formats: buffet, plated, and grazing stations\n\n## Budget Breakdown\n\n*Note: The events budget file was not accessible. Please provide budget constraints for accurate costing.*\n\n### Estimated Cost Categories:\n1. **Venue Rental**: $5,000 - $20,000 (depending on venue and duration)\n2. **Accommodations**: $200 - $400 per person per night\n3. **Catering**: $75 - $150 per person per day\n4. **Transportation**: $2,000 - $5,000 (depending on group size)\n5. **Activities & Team Building**: $3,000 - $10,000\n6. **Audio/Visual Equipment**: $1,000 - $5,000\n7. **Miscellaneous**: $2,000 - $5,000\n\n### Total Estimated Budget Range: $25,000 - $75,000\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Finalize attendee count and dates\n2. Obtain detailed dietary requirements from all team members\n3. Confirm available budget for the retreat\n4. Schedule site visits to top venue candidates\n5. Develop detailed agenda and activity plan\n\n## Recommended Timeline\n- 3-4 months prior: Venue selection and booking\n- 2 months prior: Finalize catering and activities\n- 1 month prior: Send detailed information to all attendees\n- 2 weeks prior: Final confirmation and dietary requirements collection\n\n## Contact Information\nPlease reach out to discuss any of these options or to provide the budget and dietary information needed to move forward with planning."
