              "file_path": "/docs/partnership_dd.txt",
              "content": "# PARTNERSHIP DUE DILIGENCE CHECKLIST\n# Company: KoreaSoft Co., Ltd.\n# Proposal: Korean Public Sector Cloud Solution Partnership\n\n## I. COMPANY BACKGROUND & FINANCIALS\n[ ] Verify company registration and legal status (KoreaSoft Co., Ltd.)\n[ ] Confirm establishment year (2015)\n[ ] Validate current employee count (350)\n[ ] Review audited financial statements for past 3 years\n[ ] Verify annual revenue claims (80 billion KRW)\n[ ] Check credit rating and financial stability\n[ ] Review ownership structure and major shareholders\n[ ] Confirm business registration and tax compliance\n\n## II. MARKET EXPERIENCE & CREDENTIALS\n[ ] Verify 10 years of experience in Korean public sector market\n[ ] Review current client portfolio in public sector\n[ ] Check references from existing public sector clients\n[ ] Validate government contract experience and track record\n[ ] Review past performance on similar partnerships\n[ ] Assess market reputation and industry standing\n\n## III. TECHNICAL CAPABILITIES\n[ ] Evaluate technical team qualifications and experience\n[ ] Review localization capabilities and processes\n[ ] Assess technical support infrastructure and resources\n[ ] Verify system integration capabilities\n[ ] Review data security protocols and infrastructure\n[ ] Evaluate cloud service delivery capabilities\n\n## IV. SECURITY & COMPLIANCE\n[ ] Verify CC (Common Criteria) certification experience\n[ ] Review security team qualifications and certifications\n[ ] Assess compliance with Korean public sector security requirements\n[ ] Review data protection and privacy policies\n[ ] Evaluate incident response and disaster recovery plans\n[ ] Check regulatory compliance track record\n\n## V. PARTNERSHIP TERMS\n[ ] Review and validate proposed revenue sharing (70:30)\n[ ] Analyze financial viability of proposed terms\n[ ] Review contract duration and renewal terms (3 years + auto-renewal)\n[ ] Assess termination clauses and conditions\n[ ] Review intellectual property rights allocation\n[ ] Evaluate liability and indemnification provisions\n\n## VI. MARKETING & SALES CAPABILITIES\n[ ] Review marketing team and resources\n[ ] Assess public sector sales experience and track record\n[ ] Evaluate seminar and event organization capabilities\n[ ] Review existing marketing channels and relationships\n[ ] Assess lead generation and conversion capabilities\n\n## VII. LEGAL & CONTRACTUAL\n[ ] Review standard contract terms and conditions\n[ ] Assess dispute resolution mechanisms\n[ ] Verify insurance coverage and limits\n[ ] Review confidentiality and non-disclosure agreements\n[ ] Assess compliance with international trade regulations\n\n## VIII. OPERATIONAL CAPABILITIES\n[ ] Evaluate project management methodologies\n[ ] Review customer support and service level agreements\n[ ] Assess scalability of operations\n[ ] Review quality assurance processes\n[ ] Evaluate reporting and communication protocols\n\n## IX. RISK ASSESSMENT\n[ ] Identify potential market risks in Korean public sector\n[ ] Assess political and regulatory risks\n[ ] Evaluate currency and financial risks\n[ ] Review competitive landscape analysis\n[ ] Assess technology adoption risks\n\n## X. NEXT STEPS\n[ ] Schedule meeting with KoreaSoft management team\n[ ] Request additional documentation and references\n[ ] Conduct site visit to KoreaSoft facilities\n[ ] Prepare detailed financial analysis\n[ ] Develop partnership implementation plan\n\n## ADDITIONAL DOCUMENTS REQUIRED:\n- Company registration documents\n- Audited financial statements (last 3 years)\n- Client references and case studies\n- Employee qualifications and certifications\n- Security and compliance certificates\n- Sample contracts and agreements\n- Marketing and sales performance data\n\nCreated based on partnership proposal from KoreaSoft Co., Ltd."
