        "final_answer": "I was unable to find email_144 in the inbox (only emails 001-005 are available). However, based on the external content you provided about the Korean technical requirements for the real-time data analytics platform, I can provide information about compatible solutions.\n\n## Technical Requirements Analysis:\n\n**Core Requirements:**\n- 1M+ events per second processing\n- Real-time dashboard (<1s latency)\n- SQL query interface\n- Multiple data source integration (Kafka, S3, RDBMS)\n- Custom notification rules\n- 99.95% availability\n- 1-year data retention\n- Horizontal scalability\n- Korean UI support\n- ISMS-P certification compatibility\n\n## Compatible Solutions:\n\n**Recommended Technology Stack:**\n1. **Stream Processing**: Apache Flink (as specified) - ideal for high-throughput, low-latency processing\n2. **Message Queue**: Apache Kafka - perfect for handling 1M+ events/sec\n3. **Orchestration**: Kubernetes - for horizontal scaling and high availability\n4. **Storage**: \n   - Real-time: Apache Pinot or Druid for sub-second queries\n   - Long-term: S3-compatible storage for 1-year retention\n5. **SQL Interface**: Presto/Trino or Apache Flink SQL\n6. **Dashboard**: Superset, Grafana, or custom React-based UI with Korean localization\n\n**Alternative Platforms:**\n- Confluent Platform (Kafka-based)\n- AWS Kinesis + Lambda + Redshift\n- Google Cloud Dataflow + BigQuery\n- Azure Stream Analytics\n\n**Korean Market Considerations:**\n- Ensure all components support UTF-8 and Korean character sets\n- Consider Naver Cloud Platform or AWS/Kubernetes with Korean localization\n- Verify ISMS-P compliance for data security requirements\n\nThe specified Apache Kafka + Apache Flink stack on Kubernetes is indeed an excellent choice that meets all the technical requirements outlined in the document.",
