              "content": "AGILE METHODOLOGY SUMMARY\n\nAgile methodology is an iterative approach to software development and project management that emphasizes flexibility, collaboration, and customer satisfaction.\n\nKey Components:\n- Iterative Development: Work is broken down into small, manageable cycles called sprints\n- Sprints: Time-boxed periods (typically 1-4 weeks) where specific work is completed\n- Standups: Daily meetings where team members discuss progress, plans, and obstacles\n- Retrospectives: Regular meetings to reflect on what went well and what can be improved\n\nCore Principles:\n- Continuous delivery of working software\n- Adapting to changing requirements\n- Close collaboration between developers and business stakeholders\n- Regular reflection and process improvement\n\nBenefits:\n- Faster response to changing requirements\n- Higher quality through continuous feedback\n- Improved team collaboration and communication\n- Better risk management through incremental progress\n\nAgile methodology helps teams deliver value to customers more quickly and adapt to changing needs throughout the development process."
